The paper discusses the use of statistical significance tests in research assessments, which is relevant to several sub-fields in computer science. The focus on citation indicators suggests a connection to information retrieval (cs.IR), while the discussion of statistical significance and critical thinking is relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and statistics (cs.ST). The paper also touches on issues of randomness and null hypotheses, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and social networks (cs.SI).
